After reading VAElynx's post, I understand the article and admire its unique approach and ideas. What I can't admire is the amount of filler. This section

Calculations suggest the graphene shells can be treated as a composite material in a metastable state with a mean of 105 ± 103 defects at its current temperature and pressure. At 70GPa-msec.

